ing: 2 (15.5 ounce) cans French cut green beans, drained
des: "This recipe has been a childhood favorite of mine, and now I make it every time I want to spice up my side dish!"
ins: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onions, and cook for a few minutes. When the onions are soft, add the garlic, and cook until fragrant. Mix in the green beans; cook and stir for two minutes. Stir in the tomato paste and water, then season with salt, pepper and cumin. Simmer for 5 more minutes over low heat before serving.
